column5: 20 days till our annual flyin trip to diamond lake , temagami Ontario. cant wait . menu done shopping list made know have to go out and do the shopping for trip
How do you get in there? any outfitters? I was trying to get west into the temagami lakes and can't find much info. Thanks in advance.
Or even camp sites n launches?
Somewhere on the net there used to be a blog chronicling one groups trips to that camp over the years. If you could find it I'm you'd find it helpful. Good luck on your trip!

Here you go a free online map with marked portages and campsites for the entire Temagami area http://www.thetemagamimap.com/ I also highly recommend the Friends of Temagami Map http://www.friendsoftemagami.org/. Diamond lake is readily accessable by portage or snowmobile in the winter.

we are staying at an out post cabin with wishinyouwerefishin.com wishin you were fishin they have an outpost cabin in diamond lake and mosquito lake rick and Pauline lockhart awesome hosts been going there for 30 yrs

Somewhere on the net there used to be a blog chronicling one groups trips to that camp over the years. If you could find it I'm you'd find it helpful. Good luck on your trip! That's funny.  I was just going through all my bookmarks to try and find that blog.  I thought it was interesting, especially since it's an "old school Netscape era" website.   Couldn't find it though.
I (and likely some others too) would love to hear about your past trips to Diamond. Pictures are cool too.
Well make sure Jim doesn't drop your beer and Darren gets you there safe!
Darren and Lakeland always get us in and out safe Darren is a great pilot and friend over the years the old web page from the diamond lake gang took it down a few years ago
